FT  23 MAR 93 / Australian Reserve Bank says it will act to cut official
cash rates
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   SYDNEY
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
The Reserve Bank of Australia said early today it would act in the money
market to cut official cash rates to around 5.25 per cent from 5.75 per
cent, Reuter reports from Sydney. The bank also cut its rediscount rate, the
rate it pays on Treasury notes prior to maturity, from 6.25 to 5.75 per
cent.
Mr Bernie Fraser, the bank's governor, said reductions in bank and other
interest rates could be expected to follow the cut, which was widely
expected by financial markets.
