<HEADLINE>
FT  23 MAR 93 / The Lex Column: Baltica/Hafnia
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Baltica's announcement that it plans to bid for Hafnia looks like an attempt
to find a Danish solution to this troubled insurance affair. Since the
underlying insurance business of both companies is sound, a merger must be
tempting - especially given a restructuring plan that should isolate the
problems in Baltica's holding company.
The main losers from this latest twist in the saga appear to be investors in
Baltica Holding, including the French Groupe Victoire. The main gainers
would be bank lenders such as Den Danske Bank whose exposure to both
companies would be more secure. That begs the question, though, of who will
be rash enough to recapitalise Baltica so that it can take over Hafnia. If
this really is a local solution, Danish pension funds might stump up the
cash. But a lot of Scandinavian institutional money has already been wasted
on grandiose schemes in the financial sector.
</TEXT>
