FT  23 MAR 93 / UK Company News: Frogmore slides 4% to Pounds 4m
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By HUGH CARNEGY
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
LITIGATION COSTS and increased interest charges held back interim profits at
Frogmore Estates, the property company.
At the pre-tax level they fell 4 per cent to Pounds 4.16m in the six months
to December 31.
Turnover rose 30 per cent to Pounds 22.2m on the back of a sharply increased
rent roll, which grew from Pounds 13.5m to Pounds 18m through acquisitions,
rent reviews and new lettings.
Interest charges, however, rose from Pounds 700,000 to Pounds 2.5m.
Borrowings at the end of December stood at Pounds 55m, compared to Pounds
45.8m at the end of June and Pounds 7m the previous December. Frogmore
de-geared heavily as the property recession bit, but has since taken on new
borrowing.
Frogmore also included a Pounds 1.5m charge for litigation costs arising
from a dispute over the acquisition of Land Investors by BCPH in 1986. Mr
David Wilmot, finance director, said the issue was now closed and no further
costs would be incurred.
Earnings per share were 6.9p (7.5p). The interim dividend is 3.6p (3.4p).
