FT  23 MAR 93 / International Capital Markets: Andean Fund plans Dollars 75m
issue
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By STEPHEN FIDLER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
THE Andean Development Fund, awarded last week an investment-grade rating by
Standard &amp; Poor's, is planning a Eurodollar bond issue next month if market
conditions permit.
The BBB rating for the fund - known by its Spanish acronym CAF and owned by
the governments of Bolivia, Colombia, Ecuador, Peru and Venezuela - makes it
the second Latin borrower to achieve investment grade status. The other is
the government of Chile, which was awarded the same rating last year and is
unlikely to be an active borrower.
Mr Enrique Garcia, the fund's executive president, said a Dollars 75m
five-year issue - its first in the public bond markets - was planned next
month, with Chemical Bank as lead underwriter.
The fund wants to make further bond issues this year in other markets, such
as the Yankee bond market in the US and Japan's Samurai market.
