<HEADLINE>
FT  22 MAR 93 / UK Company News: Channel Hldgs expands its security side
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JEAN MARSHALL
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Channel Holdings, the former investment company known as Channel Tunnel
Investments, is taking a further step in transforming itself into an
industrial group with the acquisition of CQR, a security alarm maker, from
Expamet International, for Pounds 1.72m in cash.
Because of the size of the transaction CH requested a halt to dealings in
the company's shares on Friday. They stood at 25p.
Under the deal Channel has also agreed to procure that CQR repays Pounds
2.08m inter-company debt to Expamet. Also, on completion, CQR will repay a
Pounds 647,000 loan to Expamet from its own resources.
To finance the acquisition Channel proposes to raise about Pounds 4.1m by
way of a placing of 8.74m new ordinary shares and a rights issue of 9.09m
new ordinary, both at 23p per share. The rights will be on the basis of
3-for-5 ordinary and 3-for-1 preference shares.
This acquisition follows the purchase of Carflow Products last August.
</TEXT>
