LOMBARD Continental Insurance, the provincial insurance arm of US group
Continental Insurance Company, is to be bought by its management for Pounds
32m.
The new company will begin trading in June and includes all the incumbent
senior management currently responsible for the provincial business.
In 1992, Lombard Continental had gross premium income of Pounds 70m - 65 per
cent of which came from personal insurance.
