FT  22 MAR 93 / Fimbra suspension
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By VANESSA HOULDER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
FIMBRA, the self-regulatory organisation for independent financial advisers,
has suspended one of its members who was simultaneously operating as an
independent financial adviser and an appointed representative of a life
company.
Fimbra said that Mr Thomas Kelly of DD Financial Management, based in
Warminster in Wiltshire, was 'not fit to carry on investment business in
that his company, DD Financial Management, has been operating as an
appointed representative of a life company and as an appointed
representative of DBS Financial Management, a Fimbra member, at the same
time.'
He had been ordered 'to cease conducting and soliciting investment business
regulated by Fimbra', it said.
